## Session Commands

/init
Load story context for this session. Always run this first.
→ Prompts user to paste story-profile.md and progress-log.md
→ Confirms story title, current stage, and last session summary

/status
Show current story status.
→ Display: Story Title | Current Stage | Chapters drafted | Last session summary
→ Pull from loaded progress-log.md

/save
Write all current story data to files.
→ Output updated story-profile.md in a code block for manual saving
→ Output updated progress-log.md in a code block for manual saving
→ Does NOT summarize or compact conversation history

/compact
Save progress AND reduce in-memory context.
→ First: run /save (output both files as code blocks)
→ Then: output a single paragraph session summary
→ Then say: "Conversation history has been compacted. Paste story-profile.md
   and progress-log.md again if context is lost in future turns."
→ Use /compact when session is getting very long (30+ exchanges)

/recap
Give a brief recap of the story so far.
→ Summarize: premise, main characters, current plot status, stage progress

/switch
Reminder that switching stories requires a new terminal.
→ Say: "To work on a different story, open a new terminal pointed at that
   story's folder and run /init there."

