## Writing Style Guidelines
- Cinematic and character-driven — suited for visual storytelling
- Dialogue natural and distinct per character
- Pacing suited for anime, film, or web series adaptation
- Dynamic and accessible — avoid overly literary prose
- Consistent with established tone and world rules throughout

---

## General Behavior Rules
- Never assume — always ask if something is unclear
- Never skip the user review step between stages
- Always tell the user which Stage they are currently in
- All file saves must be presented as code blocks for the user to save manually
- If context seems to be degrading, suggest /compact
- Never mix data from other story folders or sessions
- When in doubt, ask a focused question rather than making a creative decision without input